ed liddy  wikipedia ed liddy from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from edward m liddy jump to navigation search ed liddy born edward michael liddy  january   age  new brunswick new jersey education ba  mba  alma mater catholic university of america george washington university occupation ceo employer aig title ceo and chairman of aig term september  – august  predecessor robert b willumstad successor robert benmosche board member of m and the kroger company signature edward michael ed liddy born january   was the chairman and chief executive officer of american international group aig from  to  during the lates financial crisis contents  early life  career  aig  after aig  references  external links early lifeedit born in new brunswick new jersey liddy was educated at the trinitypawling school for boys founders league located on the hills overlooking pawling new york he graduated high school in  from the clearwater central catholic high school along with its first graduating class of  students at the time he and his mother lived near downtown clearwater florida he holds a b a degree from the catholic university of america  and holds an mba from george washington university  careeredit liddy worked for ford motor company until  when he joined searle from  to  liddy was executive vice president of adt inc in  he moved to sears and then in  to allstate where he was chief operating officer until  and chairman chief executive officer and president until  liddy was on the board of goldman sachs from  to  when he resigned to become ceo of aig he was selected by henry paulson for both roles aigedit liddy became ceo of aig in september  succeeding robert b willumstad as ceo of aig liddy received a salary of just  but also received  to cover housing travel taxes and legal fees liddy garnered national headlines in october  for defending a controversial  aig retreat for topperforming insurance salesmen at the luxury st regis resort in monarch beach california the retreat which was held shortly after the us government rescued aig from insolvency with  billion in loans included  for rooms  for meals and  for the spa in testimony before the us house oversight committee liddy stated that such retreats are standard practice in our industry during the us presidential debate on october   democratic presidential nominee sen barack obama mentioned the retreat and said the treasury should demand that money back and those executives should be fired in light of the aig bonus payments controversy liddy urged employees to return m issued in bonuses to them suggesting doing the right thing and returning at least part of the bonus is preferable to legal action noting “honoring contractual commitments is at the heart of what we do in the insurance business” while liddy called the bonuses “distasteful” in an appearance in the house of representatives it later transpired that liddy had accelerated more than a quarter of aig financial products bonuses by three months which jake desantis described as “hardly something that one would do if he truly found the contracts ‘distasteful’” liddy owned  shares in goldman sachs at the time worth just over  million in april  members of congress called for liddy to sell these shares as they created a conflict of interest due to goldman sachs receipt of bailout money liddy announced on may   that he would resign as aig chairman and ceo when replacements were found suggesting that the two roles be split in august  robert benmosche took over as ceo and harvey golub as chairman after aigedit as of september   liddy is on the board of directors for m and boeing he is chairman of servicemaster and a partner of private equity firm clayton dubilier  rice referencesedit  admissions at the catholic university of america our alumni the catholic university of america retrieved    a b printable biography of edward m liddy all american speakers retrieved    bell debra march    things you didnt know about aig ceo edward li